def calculate_max_mean_sum(n, n1, n2, wealths):
    wealths.sort()
    less = min(n1, n2)
    more = max(n1, n2)
    sum1 = sum(wealths[-less:])
    sum2 = sum(wealths[-(less + more):-less])
    result = sum1 / less - sum2 / more
    return result
